      "text": "ARMY FACTION MUSTERING RULES FORMING BOARDING SQUADS RULES ADAPTATIONS ARMY RULE DETACHMENT RULE ENHANCEMENTS CHARACTER STRATAGEMS Due to the distinct nature of close-quarters battle in Boarding Actions, most army rules require some modifications to their effects. Where this is the case, these will be described here. Each faction will have a number of different Detachments to choose from, each with its own Detachment rule to reflect the unique fighting methods of such forces. Further Enhancements that you can give to models from your army, beyond those( ), will be found here. Additional Stratagems that you can use, in addition to those ( ), will be found here. A keyword that will be shared by all units in your army. Which units you are allowed to include in your army. Any additional rules that will apply in the missions step. Note that not all Detachments will have these. Some units will be unable to use certain abilities in Boarding Actions battles. Where this is the case, these units and their relevant abilities will be listed here. [Khaine’s Arrow] Honed to a single, perfect point, the Aeldari Aspect Warriors streak across the void of space aboard Vampire Raiders before plunging deep into the heart of the enemy ship. Perhaps they strike the bridge. Maybe they pierce the defences of the enginarium. Wherever they hit home, they bring doom to the foe. [Mustering a Boarding Patrol] You can include up to one of the following units: You can include up to one of the following units: You can include up to one of each of the following units: You can include up to one of the following units: You can include up to one of the following unit: [Rules Adaptations] [Army Rule] [Seers’ Guidance] Command Re-roll Units from your army with the Strands of Fate ability replace that ability with this one. Once per , you can target one unit from your army with this ability with the Stratagem for 0CP. [Detachment Rule] [Unerring Strike] AELDARI Normal move AELDARI In your , each time an unit from your army makes a , while making that move it can attempt to operate a closed that is within 1\" of it at any point during that move, provided there are no enemy units within 1\" of that Hatchway. If that unit does attempt to operate that Hatchway, reduce the distance each model in that unit can move this phase by 2\" (if this makes it impossible for that unit to gel within 1\" of that Hatchway it wishes to operate, then it cannot attempt to do so), and it cannot again this turn."
