      "name": "Introduction",
      "text": "ARMY FACTION MUSTERING RULES FORMING BOARDING SQUADS RULES ADAPTATIONS ARMY RULE DETACHMENT RULE ENHANCEMENTS CHARACTER STRATAGEMS Due to the distinct nature of close-quarters battle in Boarding Actions, most army rules require some modifications to their effects. Where this is the case, these will be described here. Each faction will have a number of different Detachments to choose from, each with its own Detachment rule to reflect the unique fighting methods of such forces. Further Enhancements that you can give to models from your army, beyond those( ), will be found here. Additional Stratagems that you can use, in addition to those ( ), will be found here. A keyword that will be shared by all units in your army. Which units you are allowed to include in your army. Any additional rules that will apply in the missions step. Note that not all Detachments will have these. Some units will be unable to use certain abilities in Boarding Actions battles. Where this is the case, these units and their relevant abilities will be listed here. [Embarked Regiment] Astra Militarum regiments spend months, even years, travelling aboard voidships between war zones. Many fortify their billets during such long periods of inactivity, whether against the danger of hostile boarders, or to hide illicit activities from prying discipline masters! [Mustering a Boarding Patrol] PLATOON COMMAND SQUAD You can include up to one of the following units: You can include up to one of the following units: You can include up to three of each of the following units: (10 models) (10 models) (10 models) (10 models) You can include up to one of each of the following units: (3 models) (5 or 10 models) (5 models) (3 models) [Forming Boarding Squads] [Rules Adaptations] [Army Rule] [Direct Orders] Voice Command OFFICER issues Order ASTRA MILITARUM Units from your army with the ability retain that ability and gain this one. Each time an model in this unit , that Order can be issued to any one friendly unit within range, regardless of any keywords that unit is normally required to have. [Detachment Rule] [Get Down!] ASTRA MILITARUM ASTRA MILITARUM OGRYN Each time an unit from your army is selected to shoot, you can select one other friendly unit (excluding units). Until the end of the phase, models in the attacking unit can ignore models in that friendly unit for the purposes of"
