      "name": "Introduction",
      "text": "ARMY FACTION MUSTERING RULES FORMING BOARDING SQUADS RULES ADAPTATIONS ARMY RULE DETACHMENT RULE ENHANCEMENTS CHARACTER STRATAGEMS Due to the distinct nature of close-quarters battle in Boarding Actions, most army rules require some modifications to their effects. Where this is the case, these will be described here. Each faction will have a number of different Detachments to choose from, each with its own Detachment rule to reflect the unique fighting methods of such forces. Further Enhancements that you can give to models from your army, beyond those( ), will be found here. Additional Stratagems that you can use, in addition to those ( ), will be found here. A keyword that will be shared by all units in your army. Which units you are allowed to include in your army. Any additional rules that will apply in the missions step. Note that not all Detachments will have these. Some units will be unable to use certain abilities in Boarding Actions battles. Where this is the case, these units and their relevant abilities will be listed here. [Boarding Strike] Space Marines excel in the sort of fast-paced, ferociously violent battles that erupt during voidship boarding assaults. Moving fast and hitting hard, they swiftly secure enemy vessels, or else sweep impertinent foes from their own warships’ decks. [Mustering a Boarding Patrol] ADEPTUS ASTARTES Chapter All of the models in your Boarding Patrol must be drawn from the same You can include up to two of the following units (duplicates are not allowed): You can include up to three of each of the following units: You can include up to one of each of the following units: You can include up to one of the following units: You can include up to one of the following units: [Rules Adaptations] Units that can lose the ability. [Army Rule] Oath Moment Units from your army with the ability retain that ability. [Detachment Rule] [Drive Home the Blade] ADEPTUS ASTARTES [sustained hits"
