      "name": "Introduction",
      "text": "ARMY FACTION MUSTERING RULES FORMING BOARDING SQUADS RULES ADAPTATIONS ARMY RULE DETACHMENT RULE ENHANCEMENTS CHARACTER STRATAGEMS Due to the distinct nature of close-quarters battle in Boarding Actions, most army rules require some modifications to their effects. Where this is the case, these will be described here. Each faction will have a number of different Detachments to choose from, each with its own Detachment rule to reflect the unique fighting methods of such forces. Further Enhancements that you can give to models from your army, beyond those( ), will be found here. Additional Stratagems that you can use, in addition to those ( ), will be found here. A keyword that will be shared by all units in your army. Which units you are allowed to include in your army. Any additional rules that will apply in the missions step. Note that not all Detachments will have these. Some units will be unable to use certain abilities in Boarding Actions battles. Where this is the case, these units and their relevant abilities will be listed here. [Starfire Cadre] When mobilised en masse for shipboard warfare, the interconnected teams of a Starfire Cadre are swiftly moved into position by Air caste assets before commencing aggressive sweep-and-clear operations. [Mustering a Boarding Patrol] You can include up to two of the following unit (duplicate are not allowed): You can include up to three of each of the following units: You can include up to one of each of the following unit: You can include up to one of the following unit : [Forming Boarding Squads] [Rules Adaptations] [Army Rule] [Void Combat Discipline] Greater Good T’AU EMPIRE Advanced Fell Back Units from your army with the ability lose that ability and units from your army gain this one. Each time a model in this unit makes a ranged attack, it can ignore other model in this unit for the purpose of . In addition, this unit is eligible to perform the Tactical Manoeuvre in a turn in which it [Detachment Rule] [Markerlight Precision] T’AU EMPIRE KROOT [SUSTAINED HITS MARKERLIGHT Each time a unit from your army (excluding units) is selected to shoot, ranged weapons equipped by models in your unit have their Ballistic Skill characteristic improved by 1 and have the ability while targeting an enemy unit that is to one or more friendly units that are not within of one or more enemy models."
